

Installation
------------

hg clone http://r.cs.purdue.edu/hg/fastr
hg clone --insecure https://maxinevm@lafo.ssw.uni-linz.ac.at/hg/graalvm-truffle

cd graalvm-truffle
echo "../fastr" > mx/includes

./mx.sh build

Running
-------

Using HotSpot ./mx.sh r
Using Graal ./mx.sh rg


Earlier documentation (to be merged in/updated):
------------------------------------------------


# Installation

 -  Preparing your project, i.e., create a fresh directory (for instance `fastr`)

    ~~~~
		mkdir fastr && cd fastr
    ~~~~

 -  Get sources:

    ~~~~
hg clone https://maxinevm@lafo.ssw.uni-linz.ac.at/hg/graalvm-truffle-codegen truffle
hg clone http://r.cs.purdue.edu/hg/fastr
    ~~~~

 -  Patch mx (until my changes are merged):

    ~~~~
wget http://www.cs.purdue.edu/homes/fmoranda/dist/mx-overlay.patch -O- | patch -d truffle -p1
    ~~~~

 -  Configure (Eclipse/Netbeans/IntelliJ)

    ~~~~
export MX_PROJECTS_OVERLAY=../fastr/mx
cd truffle && ./mx.sh ideinit
    ~~~~

     + Eclipse: Switch to your new workspace (your fresh new dir, remember `fastr`), Import \\ Existing projects \\ Select your fresh new dir
     + IntelliJ: Shams, any ideas ?
     + NetBeans: People are still using this ?

